[{"text": "\"The sun will come out tomorrow...\"", "start": 6.873, "duration": 6.34}, {"text": "That star at the center of our Solar System,", "start": 20.52, "duration": 3.203}, {"text": "that superhot ball of plasma", "start": 23.723, "duration": 1.835}, {"text": "that gives us heat and energy,", "start": 25.558, "duration": 2.203}, {"text": "and amazing complexions...", "start": 27.761, "duration": 1.568}, {"text": "well, it's a ticking time bomb.", "start": 33.233, "duration": 3.97}, {"text": "After that, the Sun will expand,", "start": 45.145, "duration": 2.602}, {"text": "becoming a red giant.", "start": 47.747, "duration": 2.369}, {"text": "Then it will shrink to become a white dwarf,", "start": 50.116, "duration": 4.038}, {"text": "a dying star,", "start": 54.154, "duration": 1.334}, {"text": "cooling for the next several billion years.", "start": 55.488, "duration": 3.037}, {"text": "Of course, we'll all be long gone", "start": 58.525, "duration": 2.335}, {"text": "before any of that happens. But,", "start": 60.86, "duration": 2.002}, {"text": "still, can you imagine what it would be like", "start": 62.862, "duration": 2.97}, {"text": "to watch the Sun blow up", "start": 65.832, "duration": 1.602}, {"text": "before your very eyes?", "start": 67.434, "duration": 2.602}, {"text": "With a name like 'Supernova,'", "start": 70.036, "duration": 2.102}, {"text": "you'd think that a solar explosion would be", "start": 72.138, "duration": 2.503}, {"text": "the most magnificent fireworks show", "start": 74.641, "duration": 2.536}, {"text": "the world has ever seen.", "start": 77.177, "duration": 2.636}, {"text": "But in reality,", "start": 79.813, "duration": 1.201}, {"text": "you likely wouldn't see anything! ", "start": 81.481, "duration": 1.568}, {"text": "The Sun is 150 million km (93 million miles)", "start": 83.683, "duration": 3.971}, {"text": "away from Earth,", "start": 87.654, "duration": 1.768}, {"text": "and it takes 8 minutes for light", "start": 89.422, "duration": 2.102}, {"text": "from the Sun to reach us.", "start": 91.524, "duration": 2.336}, {"text": "And while that may seem super far away,", "start": 93.86, "duration": 3.437}, {"text": "in supernova terms,", "start": 97.297, "duration": 2.035}, {"text": "we don't stand a chance.", "start": 99.332, "duration": 2.536}, {"text": "For Earth to be completely safe", "start": 101.868, "duration": 2.97}, {"text": "from a supernova,", "start": 104.838, "duration": 1.134}, {"text": "we'd need to be at least", "start": 105.972, "duration": 1.034}, {"text": "50 to 100 light-years away!", "start": 107.006, "duration": 3.604}, {"text": "But the good news is that,", "start": 110.61, "duration": 1.668}, {"text": "if the Sun were to explode tomorrow,", "start": 112.278, "duration": 2.536}, {"text": "the resulting shockwave wouldn't be", "start": 114.814, "duration": 1.769}, {"text": "strong enough to destroy the whole Earth.", "start": 116.583, "duration": 2.903}, {"text": "Only the side facing the Sun", "start": 119.486, "duration": 1.868}, {"text": "would boil away instantly.", "start": 121.354, "duration": 1.702}, {"text": "The lucky other half would experience", "start": 123.456, "duration": 2.369}, {"text": "a rise in temperature that would be", "start": 125.825, "duration": 1.735}, {"text": "15 times hotter than the Sun's", "start": 127.56, "duration": 1.802}, {"text": "current surface temperature,", "start": 129.362, "duration": 1.869}, {"text": "and permanent darkness.", "start": 131.231, "duration": 1.635}, {"text": "And without the Sun's mass keeping us in orbit,", "start": 136.169, "duration": 2.903}, {"text": "Earth would likely start", "start": 139.072, "duration": 1.268}, {"text": "floating off into in space", "start": 140.34, "duration": 2.102}, {"text": "while its remaining inhabitants", "start": 142.442, "duration": 1.468}, {"text": "desperately struggle to stay alive.", "start": 143.91, "duration": 3.403}, {"text": "There's a chance that our planet", "start": 147.313, "duration": 2.069}, {"text": "could lock into orbit around another star", "start": 149.382, "duration": 2.469}, {"text": "that might provide", "start": 151.851, "duration": 0.868}, {"text": "the same light and heat as our Sun.", "start": 152.719, "duration": 3.17}, {"text": "But by the time that happened,", "start": 155.889, "duration": 1.768}, {"text": "we'd all be long gone.", "start": 157.657, "duration": 2.669}, {"text": "If we knew in advance the day that", "start": 160.326, "duration": 2.169}, {"text": "the Sun would explode,", "start": 162.495, "duration": 1.735}, {"text": "then we could buy ourselves", "start": 164.23, "duration": 1.869}, {"text": "as many as 1,000 years of time,", "start": 166.099, "duration": 2.736}, {"text": "provided we had the resources", "start": 168.835, "duration": 1.535}, {"text": "to sustain ourselves for that long.", "start": 170.37, "duration": 2.402}, {"text": "And we could!", "start": 172.772, "duration": 1.168}, {"text": "Just a few meters below", "start": 173.94, "duration": 1.368}, {"text": "the ground you walk on,", "start": 175.308, "duration": 1.401}, {"text": "the Earth is maintaining", "start": 176.709, "duration": 1.502}, {"text": "a temperature of about 17\u00b0C (62\u00b0F).", "start": 178.211, "duration": 3.27}, {"text": "So, if we had enough time to prepare,", "start": 181.481, "duration": 2.302}, {"text": "civilization could continue to live", "start": 183.783, "duration": 2.169}, {"text": "by moving underground", "start": 185.952, "duration": 1.735}, {"text": "into a huge network of fortified bunkers.", "start": 187.687, "duration": 4.204}, {"text": "Within a week after the explosion,", "start": 191.891, "duration": 1.935}, {"text": "the surface temperature on Earth", "start": 193.826, "duration": 1.402}, {"text": "would drop to -18\u00b0C (0\u00b0F).", "start": 195.228, "duration": 3.737}, {"text": "Within a year, temperatures would", "start": 198.965, "duration": 1.635}, {"text": "plummet to about -73\u00b0C (-100\u00b0F).", "start": 200.6, "duration": 3.503}, {"text": "At this point, the oceans would begin to freeze", "start": 204.103, "duration": 2.703}, {"text": "from the top down.", "start": 206.806, "duration": 1.769}, {"text": "Within 1,000 years,", "start": 208.575, "duration": 1.768}, {"text": "Earth\u2019s atmosphere would freeze and collapse,", "start": 210.343, "duration": 3.203}, {"text": "leaving anything left on the surface", "start": 213.546, "duration": 1.935}, {"text": "exposed to cosmic radiation", "start": 215.481, "duration": 2.403}, {"text": "and meteor impacts.", "start": 217.884, "duration": 1.968}, {"text": "Hopefully, by that point,", "start": 219.852, "duration": 1.569}, {"text": "we'd have found ourselves a new home.", "start": 221.421, "duration": 3.003}, {"text": "The good news is that", "start": 224.424, "duration": 1.401}, {"text": "if the Sun were to explode", "start": 225.825, "duration": 2.002}, {"text": "- and it will eventually happen -", "start": 227.827, "duration": 2.336}, {"text": "it wouldn't happen overnight.", "start": 230.163, "duration": 2.269}, {"text": "When the Sun does die,", "start": 232.432, "duration": 1.568}, {"text": "it will be a long, slow, arduous process", "start": 234.0, "duration": 3.27}, {"text": "taking place over billions of years.", "start": 237.27, "duration": 3.303}, {"text": "The Sun will get hotter and brighter,", "start": 240.573, "duration": 2.469}, {"text": "and it will start to expand.", "start": 243.042, "duration": 2.002}, {"text": "During this process,", "start": 245.044, "duration": 1.101}, {"text": "it will lose its outer layers to the cosmos,", "start": 246.145, "duration": 2.703}, {"text": "leading to the creation of", "start": 248.848, "duration": 1.402}, {"text": "other stars and planets", "start": 250.25, "duration": 1.901}, {"text": "in the same way that", "start": 252.151, "duration": 0.968}, {"text": "the violent burst of the Big Bang created Earth.", "start": 253.152, "duration": 3.604}, {"text": "Who knows? Maybe new life could form.", "start": 256.756, "duration": 3.103}, {"text": "Can you imagine another Earth?", "start": 259.859, "duration": 2.669}, {"text": "A new humanoid species?", "start": 262.528, "duration": 3.037}, {"text": "It's hard to predict how our galaxy", "start": 265.565, "duration": 2.135}, {"text": "might look billions of years from now, and,", "start": 267.7, "duration": 2.202}, {"text": "it's especially hard", "start": 269.902, "duration": 1.135}, {"text": "to imagine our solar system", "start": 271.037, "duration": 1.802}, {"text": "without the great, golden anchor", "start": 272.839, "duration": 1.768}, {"text": "that keeps it all together.", "start": 274.607, "duration": 2.269}, {"text": "But one day, in the very, very distant future,", "start": 276.876, "duration": 4.304}, {"text": "the Sun will expand,", "start": 281.18, "duration": 1.969}, {"text": "and then it will shrink,", "start": 283.149, "duration": 2.336}, {"text": "maybe leaving room for", "start": 285.485, "duration": 1.535}, {"text": "a new star to take its place.", "start": 287.02, "duration": 2.736}, {"text": "And if, by some miracle,", "start": 289.756, "duration": 1.902}, {"text": "humanity still exists at that point,", "start": 291.658, "duration": 2.569}, {"text": "where might we be living?", "start": 294.227, "duration": 2.369}, {"text": "Can you imagine your descendants", "start": 296.596, "duration": 2.369}, {"text": "being born on a space station?", "start": 298.965, "duration": 3.07}, {"text": "Well, that's a story for another WHAT IF.", "start": 302.035, "duration": 5.772}]